==Plagiarism controversy== Media sources including [[Sina Corp|Sina]] Games and Taiwan-based ''[[Liberty Times]]'' have included comparisons between the ''Little Cherry'' animated series and the Japanese manga and anime series ''[[Chibi Maruko-chan]]'', such as their similar titles, in articles about alleged plagiarism in Chinese animation.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wang|first1=Sheng|title=「櫻桃小丸子」成了「小櫻桃和小丸子」，國產動畫山寨風能不能停|url=https://kknews.cc/comic/z6nao3.html|accessdate=2016-09-19|work=kknews.cc|date=2016-06-30|language=Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=有作品就補貼 中國姑息山寨動畫|url=http://ent.ltn.com.tw/news/breakingnews/1377577|accessdate=2016-09-19|work=Liberty Times Net|date=2015-07-13|language=Chinese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=山寨国产动画盘点 秒速五帧的抄袭速度|url=http://games.sina.com.cn/wjzx/bgqw/2015-04-24/doc-icczmvup0258833.shtml|accessdate=2016-09-19|work=Sina Games|date=2015-04-24|language=Chinese}}</ref>
