{{Infobox journal | image = <!-- or |cover= --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | former_name = Theatre Quarterly | abbreviation = New Theatre Q. | discipline = [[Theatre studies]] | language = English | editor = <!-- or |editors= --> | publisher = [[Cambridge University Press]] | country = England | history = | frequency = 4 times per year | impact = | impact-year = | ISSN = 0266-464X | eISSN = 1474-0613 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = 85643629 | OCLC = 939216787 | website = https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/new-theatre-quarterly | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> }}
'''''New Theatre Quarterly''''' ('''''NTQ''''') is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[theatre studies]]. It is published by [[Cambridge University Press]]. ''New Theatre Quarterly'' succeeds '''''Theatre Quarterly''''' (1971–81). Over the years, ''NTQ'' has developed a reputation for a "down-to-earth approach" to theatre studies.<ref name="Kershaw">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2005/apr/19/guardianobituaries.artsobituaries |title=Obituary: Clive Barker |last=Kershaw |first=Baz |date=18 April 2005 |website=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=2017-03-21}}</ref>
Its general editors are Maria Shevtsova of [[Goldsmiths, University of London]], and Simon Trussler of [[Rose Bruford College]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/new-theatre-quarterly |title=''New Theatre Quarterly'' |website=[[Cambridge University Press]] |location=Cambridge |access-date=2017-03-21}}</ref> Shevtsova replaced Clive Barker, who died in 2005.<ref name="Kershaw"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://theatrefutures.org.uk/blog/2012/09/05/professor-simon-trussler/ |title=Professor Simon Trussler |author=<!-- staff --> |date=5 September 2012 |website=Theatre Futures |publisher=[[Rose Bruford College]] |location=London |access-date=2017-03-21}}</ref> Trussler and Barker were the journals founding editors.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://theatrefutures.org.uk/blog/2010/04/20/new-theatre-quarterly/ |title=''New Theatre Quarterly'' |author=<!-- staff --> |date=20 April 2010 |website=Theatre Futures |publisher=Rose Bruford College |location=London |access-date=2017-03-21}}</ref>
